article.headline: Northeastern 73, James Madison 61
article.story: BOSTON -- Chaisson Allen and Matt Janning each scored 16 points to lead Northeastern to a 73-61 win over James Madison on Saturday. Baptiste Bataille had 11 points and Nkem Ojougboh finished with 10 rebounds -- six offensive -- and three blocked shots for the Huskies (6-7, 1-1 Colonial Athletic Association). Northeastern, which never trailed, scored the game's first nine points and later took a 39-19 lead -- its largest -- on a 3-pointer by Janning with 5 minutes left in the first half. The Huskies, who won their fourth straight game, shot 60 percent from the floor and scored a season-high 47 points in the first half. The Dukes (6-6, 0-2) were unable to pull any closer than 14 the rest of the way. Julius Wells led James Madison with 18 points. Pierre Curtis scored 11 points and Trevon Flores added 10.
